07/04/2004
DUBLIN, Ireland -- Greek Transport Minister Mihalis Liapis says his government is committed to implementing the EU strategic action plan to reduce by half the number of road accident victims by 2010. 
Liapis was speaking at an informal EU council meeting in Dublin on Tuesday (6 April). 
European transport ministers gathered to draft a European Charter on Road Safety in time for World Health Day on Wednesday. 
(ANA, MPA - 06/04/04)
